Alcove adapter no longer hardcodes ``rework_cycles=0``, ``findings=[]``, and a single ``"session"`` phase. Bridge-format JSON files may now include top-level ``rework_cycles`` (int), ``findings`` (list of reviewer findings), and ``phases`` (dict of named phase metadata); the adapter reads all three when present. Malformed findings are skipped gracefully, sensitive content in findings is redacted, and transcript tool-call output is placed on the last named phase. Classic Alcove sessions without these fields continue to default to zero rework cycles, empty findings, and a single ``"session"`` phase.
